1
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:15,933
So you and Yenyen
are now together?

2
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,233
What about me?

3
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,267
Sab, we can still be friends.

4
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:21,667
Red, I love you so much.

5
00:00:21,733 --> 00:00:24,367
Don't insist on things that
are not possible to happen.

6
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:27,033
I'm going to Yenyen and Raichu.

7
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,200
Wait, Red.

8
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:29,333
Oh my God!

9
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,467
We're here!

10
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:32,433
There are rescuers!
I need to tell Yenyen
and Raichu!

11
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:34,367
Hey! We're here!

12
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:36,033
- Hey, Red! Don't go.
- Wait.

13
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:38,633
-They won't see us if you leave.
-I need to tell them!

14
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,500
Wait! We're here!

15
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:41,500
Mister!

16
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:44,300
Raichu!

17
00:00:44,367 --> 00:00:45,333
Yenyen!

18
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,000
Red, we have to go back.

19
00:00:51,067 --> 00:00:54,000
The rescuers might leave!

20
00:00:54,067 --> 00:00:57,067
I'm not leaving without Yenyen!

21
00:00:57,133 --> 00:00:58,100
Raichu!

22
00:00:58,167 --> 00:00:58,967
Eden!

23
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:01,700
Thank God you're here!

24
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:03,033
Yen!

25
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:04,067
Babe!

26
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:14,600
Thank you, Eden.

27
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:15,733
Roger, roger.

28
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:18,733
We found two survivors
on a nearby island.

29
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,133
We're heading back
to the headquarters.

30
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,900
Mister, please hurry!

31
00:01:21,967 --> 00:01:23,367
We're the only ones here.

32
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:24,367
Please, Mister.

33
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:27,300
Eden, I thought I was going
to die.

34
00:01:27,367 --> 00:01:29,533
What were you doing up there?

35
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:33,267
Raichu, did you hear that?

36
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:35,467
Is that a boat that I hear?

37
00:01:37,533 --> 00:01:38,733
I think there's a boat
on the shore!

38
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,167
Come on, let's go!

39
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:45,233
Red!

40
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:47,967
Sabina!

41
00:01:49,167 --> 00:01:51,200
We're here!

42
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:52,267
Red!

43
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:54,333
To the family of the plane
crash victims,

44
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:57,167
we have a word
from the rescue team.

45
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:59,500
They found two survivors.

46
00:01:59,567 --> 00:02:02,067
One woman and one man
were found.

47
00:02:02,133 --> 00:02:03,800
Have they identified
the survivors?

48
00:02:03,867 --> 00:02:06,700
Sir, have they identified
the woman they rescued?

49
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:09,567
Please, can you wait your turn?
I asked him first!

50
00:02:09,633 --> 00:02:10,800
You're interrupting again.

51
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:13,567
For all you know, you're
daughter's already dead!

52
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:14,467
She's still alive!

53
00:02:14,567 --> 00:02:16,000
How did you know that?

54
00:02:16,067 --> 00:02:18,067
A pigeon brought me a note
from her.

55
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:19,967
Are you happy now?

56
00:02:20,033 --> 00:02:22,033
They don't care about us!

57
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,800
I'm sure he'll come back for us.

58
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:24,867
I saw this on the boat.

59
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:26,967
It might belong to one
of the survivors.

60
00:02:42,967 --> 00:02:43,900
Sir...

61
00:02:44,933 --> 00:02:49,333
Sir, have you contacted
our parents?

62
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:52,133
Especially my boyfriend's
parents?

63
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:54,267
Because he needs them.

64
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:55,433
Yes, Ma'am.

65
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,367
We've already sent a message
to the Manila office.

66
00:02:57,433 --> 00:02:59,633
We'll also take care of your
transportation back home

67
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:03,567
as soon as we get the release
order from your doctors.

68
00:03:03,633 --> 00:03:05,333
Okay, thank you.

69
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,433
Excuse me.

70
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,033
I need to go.

71
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:09,400
Thank you so much.

72
00:03:09,467 --> 00:03:10,467
Okay.

73
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:17,300
Red.

74
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,700
Are you okay?

75
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:29,800
No!

76
00:03:29,867 --> 00:03:31,867
It's all Amanda's fault!

77
00:03:31,933 --> 00:03:33,900
She stresses me out!

78
00:03:33,967 --> 00:03:35,867
Don't let her affect you.

79
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:38,133
Let's go back
to the coffee shop.

80
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,133
Victor, I don't want
to go there!

81
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,433
I want to stay here.

82
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:42,033
We might hear a word from them,
okay?

83
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:44,600
And I won't be able
to relax there.

84
00:03:44,667 --> 00:03:46,267
Can we just wait?

85
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:47,300
Okay.

86
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,333
Mr. and Mrs. Ramos, right?

87
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:53,500
Yes.

88
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,233
Are you related
to Mr. Roderick Ramos?

89
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,400
- He's our son.
- Yes.

90
00:03:56,467 --> 00:03:58,467
We got a call from Davao.

91
00:03:58,533 --> 00:03:59,433
They'll be bringing him

92
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,667
to St. Patrick's Hospital
via chopper.

93
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:02,900
-You can see him there.
-Why are they bringing him...

94
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:04,700
Why do they have to bring him
to a hospital?

95
00:04:04,767 --> 00:04:05,967
What happened to our son?

96
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:07,133
Ma'am, Sir, I'm sorry.

97
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,800
That's all the information
I can give you.

98
00:04:08,867 --> 00:04:11,300
You should go to the hospital.

99
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:12,400
What happened to Red?

100
00:04:12,467 --> 00:04:14,267
Why do they need to bring him
to the hospital?

101
00:04:14,333 --> 00:04:15,233
Let's just go there.
Red needs us.

102
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,133
Let's go and find out.

103
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,533
Let's go.

104
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,700
Zandro, let's go.

105
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:29,167
Amanda, what's going on
with your best enemy?

106
00:04:29,267 --> 00:04:30,200
I don't know.

107
00:04:30,267 --> 00:04:32,700
All I care about now is Yenyen.

108
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:36,100
I hope she's one
of the rescued survivors.

109
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:39,433
I was talking to the staff.

110
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:44,200
They found some survivors,
but Eden is not one of them.

111
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:48,467
Where could she be?

112
00:04:48,533 --> 00:04:53,100
I heard that there are a lot
of rescuers.

113
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:56,100
They said they found survivors
from other islands.

114
00:04:56,167 --> 00:04:57,933
Eden could be one of them.

115
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:01,067
I can't just wait here.

116
00:05:01,167 --> 00:05:02,800
I need to do something.

117
00:05:04,267 --> 00:05:05,833
I want to see my daughter.

118
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:16,700
We don't know when we can
get out of here.

119
00:05:20,967 --> 00:05:22,200
You know...

120
00:05:23,767 --> 00:05:25,433
I don't know too.
I have no idea.

121
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,333
Maybe they got stuck in traffic.

122
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,533
Yes, that was funny, right?

123
00:05:36,633 --> 00:05:37,633
Sorry.

124
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:41,500
We don't know what's going on.

125
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:45,967
But...

126
00:05:46,933 --> 00:05:49,467
I know that Red will come back
for us.

127
00:05:50,533 --> 00:05:51,967
I made this for you...

128
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:58,333
as a reminder that...

129
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:02,300
we will not part.

130
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,133
When will that happen?

131
00:06:09,233 --> 00:06:10,900
I want to go home.

132
00:06:10,967 --> 00:06:12,233
I do too.

133
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,567
I want to go home too.

134
00:06:13,633 --> 00:06:16,100
I want to see my mom.

135
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:19,200
But I'm sure he'll come back
for us.

136
00:06:19,267 --> 00:06:20,267
He'll look for me.

137
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:23,567
He won't abandon us
on this island.

138
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,300
Just hang in there, okay?

139
00:06:25,367 --> 00:06:28,600
Remember, never give up.

140
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:32,033
Hang in there.
We have to be patient.

141
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,333
They'll come for us.

142
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:58,867
Red?

143
00:06:58,933 --> 00:06:59,767
How are you?

144
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:01,033
How are you feeling?

145
00:07:02,367 --> 00:07:03,367
Red.

146
00:07:05,867 --> 00:07:07,033
What's wrong?

147
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:08,167
What's wrong, Red?

148
00:07:08,233 --> 00:07:09,533
My head hurts.

149
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,833
What?

150
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:11,967
Your head hurts?

151
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,267
Wait, what do I do?

152
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:16,467
What should I do?

153
00:07:16,533 --> 00:07:18,200
Should I get you up?

154
00:07:18,267 --> 00:07:19,300
Red!

155
00:07:19,367 --> 00:07:21,133
Wait, I'll get the doctor!

156
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:23,233
Doctor!

157
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:40,400
Please, help my boyfriend.
Please!

158
00:07:40,467 --> 00:07:41,900
Please, Doc.

159
00:07:41,967 --> 00:07:43,500
Red!

160
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:44,733
Red!

161
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,067
What's going on with him?
He was throwing up earlier.

162
00:07:51,433 --> 00:07:52,467
Listen.

163
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:55,267
I already ordered
that he get a CT scan.

164
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:59,100
We need to assess his condition
thoroughly.

165
00:07:59,167 --> 00:08:00,100
I'm sorry, Doc.

166
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:03,300
I'm just worried about him.

167
00:08:03,367 --> 00:08:05,600
I know. I understand where
you're coming from, okay?

168
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:07,233
Don't stress yourself.

169
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:09,433
It won't do you good.

170
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:11,133
Get some rest for now.

171
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,833
You need to regain
your strength.

172
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:16,233
You also need to get checked up.

173
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:18,233
- Okay, thank you.
- Okay.

174
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:19,733
I'll get back to you, okay?

175
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,933
Thank you.

176
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:29,033
Red, it's okay.

177
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:30,867
You're going to be fine.

178
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:34,667
It's okay. Just rest for now,
okay? I'm here.

179
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:36,633
I'm here. You're safe, okay?

180
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,667
You're safe.

181
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:41,367
I'm here.

182
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:43,700
You're safe.

183
00:08:46,433 --> 00:08:48,200
It's okay, it's okay.

184
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:53,067
What? What is it?

185
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:55,500
What?

186
00:08:55,567 --> 00:08:56,767
It's okay. You can talk to me.

187
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:59,100
What is it? Are you okay?

188
00:08:59,167 --> 00:09:00,533
How do you feel?

189
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:05,100
What?

190
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:06,167
Yenyen...

191
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:09,233
Yen.

192
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:10,433
Red.

193
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,033
Where are you, Yenyen?

194
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:17,867
- Yen, where are you?
- Red.

195
00:09:20,167 --> 00:09:21,767
Red.

196
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:22,733
Yen, where are you?

197
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:25,667
Don't worry about her for now,
please.

198
00:09:25,733 --> 00:09:27,533
We're safe now.

199
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,367
You have to get some rest
for now.

200
00:09:29,467 --> 00:09:31,567
Please, get some rest.

201
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:32,900
It's okay.

202
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:35,533
I'm here.

203
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,600
It's okay.

204
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:39,933
Yen.

205
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,000
It's okay.

206
00:09:46,567 --> 00:09:48,633
I'm sorry. It's okay.

207
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:52,133
We're safe now.

208
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,200
I'm sorry.

209
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,867
Yen, where are you?

210
00:10:02,767 --> 00:10:03,933
Here you go.

211
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,633
That's 15,000.

212
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,567
You will have to pay
10% interest every month.

213
00:10:08,633 --> 00:10:13,533
If you fail to pay once, I will
put additional interest on it.

214
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:16,100
And if you fail to pay
within two months,

215
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:17,933
I will file a complaint
against you.

216
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,267
And I will seize
your personal belongings.

217
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:22,033
Is that clear?

218
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,400
- Yes, I understand.
- Dindi...

219
00:10:24,567 --> 00:10:27,033
you're her guarantor.

220
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:29,233
If she fails to pay me back,
you will have to pay for it.

221
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,400
That won't happen, Miss Nancy.

222
00:10:32,467 --> 00:10:34,700
We will pay you back.

223
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,967
So don't worry.

224
00:10:37,033 --> 00:10:38,767
We're not delinquents.

225
00:10:43,533 --> 00:10:45,867
I hope nothing serious happened
to our son.

226
00:10:45,933 --> 00:10:47,400
Let's try to be positive.

227
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:51,100
- Is this the place?
- Auntie! Uncle!

228
00:10:51,167 --> 00:10:53,667
- Sabina!
- Hello!

229
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:55,267
I'm going to move the car.

230
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:57,733
How are you? Okay, Zandro.

231
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,600
How are you? How's my son?

232
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:01,533
So you were with him
on that island.

233
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,367
Yes, Auntie.

234
00:11:02,433 --> 00:11:03,833
But he's injured.

235
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:05,100
He's still recovering.

236
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:07,267
I want to see my son.

237
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,500
Yes, of course, Auntie.

238
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,533
He's over here.

239
00:11:13,267 --> 00:11:14,700
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

240
00:11:14,767 --> 00:11:15,733
Red.

241
00:11:18,167 --> 00:11:19,167
Red.

242
00:11:20,367 --> 00:11:22,767
Mom's here, Red.

243
00:11:22,833 --> 00:11:24,800
Doc, what happened to my son?

244
00:11:24,867 --> 00:11:25,767
How is he?

245
00:11:25,833 --> 00:11:27,767
Why is he unconscious?

246
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:31,567
Ma'am, Sir, they did an initial
test on him in Davao.

247
00:11:31,633 --> 00:11:33,567
His CT scan is also normal.

248
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:36,167
They had already stitched up
the wound on his head.

249
00:11:36,233 --> 00:11:37,200
He's under sedation right now.

250
00:11:37,267 --> 00:11:38,800
That's why he's asleep.

251
00:11:38,867 --> 00:11:41,867
We just have to observe him
within the next 72 hours.

252
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:42,933
Thank you, Doctor.

253
00:11:46,033 --> 00:11:47,533
I'm sorry about this, Dindi.

254
00:11:48,733 --> 00:11:50,667
Don't worry, I will pay it back.

255
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:52,633
Even if I have
to get another job

256
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:55,500
on top of selling rice cakes.

257
00:11:55,567 --> 00:11:57,933
I won't ruin your name.

258
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,333
Amanda, it's nothing.

259
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:03,867
We have to think of Yenyen.

260
00:12:03,933 --> 00:12:06,600
You're right.
We can't lose hope.

261
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:08,867
I'm going to Davao.

262
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:11,433
I will bring my daughter
home myself.

263
00:12:12,967 --> 00:12:14,467
She's not dead.

264
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:16,600
I can feel she's still alive.

265
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:21,833
And I know we'll be together
again.

266
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:25,767
Okay, you should go now.

267
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,000
Keep me updated, okay?

268
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:28,767
- Of course, I will.
- Stay safe, Amanda.

269
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:12,667
Darling...

270
00:13:12,733 --> 00:13:14,000
mommy's here.

271
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:19,233
You don't have to worry, okay?

272
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,133
We're here.

273
00:13:23,233 --> 00:13:25,100
We will take care of you.

274
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:29,533
We will never leave you.

275
00:13:31,567 --> 00:13:32,567
Please get better.

276
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:33,700
Get well soon.

277
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:38,700
I love you so much.

278
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:42,600
Sabina...

279
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,467
thank you.

280
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,967
Thank you for taking care
of our son.

281
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:49,133
Thank you.

282
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,267
Of course, Auntie.

283
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:54,633
I will never abandon Red,
you know that.

284
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:55,833
Sabina, thank you.

285
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:55,567
Bring those that have been
checked to the ambulance.

286
00:15:17,433 --> 00:15:19,167
Look at that tree.

287
00:15:19,233 --> 00:15:21,000
It has a lot of fruits.

288
00:15:21,067 --> 00:15:22,467
You're right. But...

289
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:26,600
it looks like Canistel fruit.

290
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:34,167
Here you go, Mom.

291
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,200
Wow!

292
00:15:38,067 --> 00:15:40,133
These are hard to find.

293
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,767
Where did you find this?

294
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:44,833
Mom, I know that
it's your favorite.

295
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:47,067
There's a tree near our house.

296
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:48,933
So I picked them for you.

297
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,400
Thank you.

298
00:15:50,467 --> 00:15:52,233
I'm sorry, Mom.

299
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:54,700
That's all I can bring you.

300
00:15:56,133 --> 00:15:58,800
I don't even know if it's sweet.

301
00:15:58,867 --> 00:16:00,033
I'm sure it's sweet.

302
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:03,033
Because you're sweet.

303
00:16:04,533 --> 00:16:05,633
And this is good enough.

304
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:07,333
These are hard to find.

305
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,733
Thank you.

306
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:12,233
You're welcome.

307
00:16:17,667 --> 00:16:20,633
It made me miss my mom more.

308
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:22,700
It's her favorite.

309
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:25,933
I hope we can go home soon,
so I can hug her.

310
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,067
We'll make it home.

311
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:30,967
Wait.

312
00:16:31,033 --> 00:16:32,267
- What are you looking for?
- My necklace!

313
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:33,767
- Your necklace?
- Yes.

314
00:16:36,867 --> 00:16:39,033
I lost it. I had it on earlier.

315
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:42,767
How are we going to find it?

316
00:16:42,867 --> 00:16:44,233
When did you have it last?

317
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:45,967
- I don't know.
- A while ago?

318
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:49,567
But I had it on earlier.
My mom gave it to me.

319
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:51,733
We have to find it.
I hope I didn't lose it.

320
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:52,900
Do you have it on earlier?

321
00:16:52,967 --> 00:16:54,700
You could have lost it here.

322
00:16:54,767 --> 00:16:55,900
Come on.

323
00:16:55,967 --> 00:16:57,667
- Let's look around here.
- Right here.

324
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:02,133
- Let's look separately.
- Right here.

325
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,633
You go that way,
and I'll go this way.

326
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:09,333
Sir, did you see a woman?

327
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,100
She's petite.

328
00:17:11,167 --> 00:17:12,200
She's tan.

329
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:13,700
She has a pretty face.

330
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:16,367
She's my daughter.

331
00:17:17,533 --> 00:17:23,567
She's wearing a necklace
with a heart pendant.

332
00:17:23,633 --> 00:17:25,700
It has her name on it.

333
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:28,900
Maybe you saw her.

334
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:30,600
Sir...

335
00:17:30,667 --> 00:17:31,600
Wait.

336
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:37,900
One of the rescuers found this.

337
00:17:43,633 --> 00:17:46,533
Sir, this is my daughter's
necklace!

338
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:51,433
I'm sure it's her necklace
because I gave this to her.

339
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:53,267
Look, that's her name.

340
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:55,833
It's written here.

341
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:57,667
Sir...

342
00:17:57,733 --> 00:18:01,833
Sir, I'm begging you.

343
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:04,567
Please, let's go to the island
where you found those survivors.

344
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:06,467
My daughter might
still be there.

345
00:18:06,533 --> 00:18:11,300
Sir, Sir, I'm begging you.

346
00:18:11,367 --> 00:18:13,167
Please, Sir.

347
00:18:13,233 --> 00:18:17,033
I know that my daughter
is still alive.

348
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:19,367
She's still alive.

349
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:23,367
Sir, Sir, please. Sir...

350
00:18:24,367 --> 00:18:25,700
Sir!

351
00:18:25,767 --> 00:18:26,833
I'm begging you.

352
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:29,433
Sorry, Ma'am.
I want to help you,

353
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,500
but civilians can't go there.

354
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:34,633
And they're putting a stop
to our rescue operation.

355
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:37,033
They said there's no survivor
left out there.

356
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:39,400
My daughter's still there.

357
00:18:39,467 --> 00:18:41,900
Let's go back to that island.

358
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:47,600
Sir, I'm begging you.

359
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:50,767
I'm begging you, please.

360
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:54,200
Please. Are you a parent?

361
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:56,933
Yes, I have one child.

362
00:18:57,033 --> 00:19:01,900
So you know how I feel.

363
00:19:01,967 --> 00:19:04,767
You won't stop until you find
your child, too, right?

364
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:07,267
Until you have your child back.

365
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:10,800
- I'm begging you, Sir.
- But...

366
00:19:10,867 --> 00:19:12,700
I will lose my job.

367
00:19:12,767 --> 00:19:14,933
Sir...

368
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,667
- But...
- Please, Sir...

369
00:19:16,733 --> 00:19:18,433
I know someone who can help you.

370
00:19:19,467 --> 00:19:21,367
He can bring you there.

371
00:19:21,433 --> 00:19:22,733
He can help us.

372
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:24,933
Let's go there.

373
00:19:35,867 --> 00:19:37,600
Yen...

374
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:39,933
Yenyen.

375
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:43,433
Yenyen, where are you? Yenyen.

376
00:19:44,567 --> 00:19:45,500
Yenyen.

377
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:48,933
Yenyen, where are you?

378
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:52,000
Yenyen?

379
00:19:55,133 --> 00:19:56,633
Yen, where are you?

380
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:57,667
Yenyen?

381
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:03,867
Who is Yenyen?

382
00:20:09,167 --> 00:20:11,767
Sabina, who's Yenyen?

383
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:14,833
Yenyen, where are you?

384
00:20:15,933 --> 00:20:16,867
Yenyen.

385
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:51,367
Let's go.

386
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:53,167
They're not coming back for us.

387
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:57,633
Red made a promise he wouldn't
leave you, didn't he?

388
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:01,733
Do you believe that
he won't abandon me?

389
00:21:03,633 --> 00:21:07,033
He should have been here by now
if he's going to save us.

390
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:12,300
We won't have to wait this long
if he's going to save us.

391
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:16,833
Raichu, I'm done waiting!

392
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:21,133
Red is gone!

393
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:25,000
He's forgotten his promise
to me!

394
00:21:25,067 --> 00:21:28,167
You give up easily.

395
00:21:28,233 --> 00:21:30,200
He's forgotten all about me.

396
00:21:31,733 --> 00:21:36,267
He has forgotten his promise
that he will never abandon me.

397
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:38,533
That we will never be apart.

398
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:40,433
I'm done!

399
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,000
I can't do this anymore!

400
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:05,000
It's Red!

401
00:23:05,067 --> 00:23:06,133
He came back!

402
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,267
Eden!

403
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:09,200
It's my mom!

404
00:23:09,267 --> 00:23:10,700
Do you hear her?

405
00:23:10,767 --> 00:23:11,800
What are you talking about?

406
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:14,200
- That's my mom!
- How can she be here?

407
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:15,800
She's in jail, remember?

408
00:23:15,867 --> 00:23:17,533
I don't know, but someone's
yelling out.

409
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:19,067
There's a boat on the shore.

410
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:20,767
It seems that nobody's here.

411
00:23:20,833 --> 00:23:22,667
We need to go back.

412
00:23:22,767 --> 00:23:25,067
I'm not leaving
without my daughter.

413
00:23:25,133 --> 00:23:26,500
We have to go there.

414
00:23:26,567 --> 00:23:27,967
Come on. Let's go look for her.

415
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:30,633
Come on, hurry!

416
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,000
What if she's not here?

417
00:23:32,067 --> 00:23:34,033
We won't know
unless we look around.

418
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:35,067
Eden!

419
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:39,433
Red?

420
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:40,867
Red, my son.

421
00:23:40,933 --> 00:23:42,933
How are you?
How are you feeling?

422
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:45,133
Where am I?

423
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,633
How did I get here?
